5|$|The general {{principle}} behind {{the process of}} qiyas {{is based on the}} understanding that every legal injunction guarantees a beneficial and welfare satisfying objective. Thus, if the cause of an injunction can be deduced from the primary sources, then analogical deduction can be applied to cases with similar causes. For example, wine is prohibited <b>in</b> <b>Islam</b> because of its intoxicating property. Thus qiyas leads to the conclusion that all intoxicants are forbidden.|$|E
